    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.0513/137: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-17T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 17, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 22—6:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. My despatch No. 661 of May 28th.<note n="8" xml:id="d10fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> Judge Crabitès submitted his resignation today as a member
                    of the Mixed Court to the Egyptian authorities. Resignation effective November
                    1st, next.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
